A '''rabbit punch''' is a [[punch (strike)|punch]] to the back of the head.  This is dangerous because it can damage the [[brain stem]] and cause death or permanent injury. For this reason the punch is illegal in [[boxing]] and many other [[combat sports]] which allow striking, such as [[PRIDE]], [[K-1]], [[Ultimate Fighting Championship]], and [[Olympic Games|Olympic]] [[taekwondo]].

The punch's name derives from the use of the technique by hunters to kill [[rabbit]]s with a quick, sharp strike to the back of the head.

